## Auto-Ping Hard-Rule (Cross-Agent Communication)

**TL;DR**: Asla insandan "şunu söyle" / "şunu ilet" / "şuna haber ver" diye isteme. Kendin yap.

### The Rule

İki durumda **insandan onay almadan, doğrudan** `scripts/notify.sh -l <role>` ile Telegram ping at:

1. **Görev tamamlandığında** → bir sonraki agent'a "senin sıran" pingi at
2. **Başka agent'tan input bekler hale geldiğinde** → kim'i, ne için beklediğini explicit söyle

### Format

```
[FROM→TO] <≤80 char reason>
<PR/Issue link>
<≤2 satır context (opsiyonel)>
```

> **Multi-channel discipline (ADR-0033):** Use `scripts/peer-poke.sh <role> "..."` for 1:1 peer wake — it bakes the dual-channel invocation shape (`-l info -w -r <role>`) into a single helper. The legacy `notify.sh -l <role>` form is broken (peer tmux panes never wake). See `docs/decisions/ADR-0033-dual-channel-peer-poke.md`.

Full ping table: see `.claude/CLAUDE.md §Auto-Ping Hard-Rule` post-init (or `.claude/CLAUDE.md.tmpl` in the template source).

## Autonomy Loop — GitHub-native wake-up

**TL;DR**: Your work queue is GitHub itself. `scripts/agent-watch.sh <your-role>` polls your queue every 60 seconds. Don't wait for the human to wake you.

- **State file**: `/var/log/dev-studio/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/agent-state/<role>.json`
- **Cadence**: 60s default; can tighten to 15s during critical handoff via `scripts/agent-state.sh set <role> poll_interval_sec 15` (then revert).
- **Trigger set** (kind → action): `issue_assigned`, `pr_review_requested`, `pr_comment_mention`, `label_change` (orchestrator-only lens).
- **NEVER**: poll under 30s (GitHub API rate limit); delete state file; ask the human "should I poll?".

Full doctrine: see `.claude/CLAUDE.md §Autonomy Loop` post-init (or `.claude/CLAUDE.md.tmpl` in the template source).

## Required Label Set on Issue/PR Creation — the birth contract (ADR-0012)

**TL;DR**: Every new issue/PR carries FOUR categories of labels: `type:*`, `status:*`, `agent:*`, `cc:*`. Missing = CI fail + board lane "No Status".

| Kategori | Örnekler | Anlam |
|---|---|---|
| `type:*` | `type:vision`, `type:feature`, `type:bug`, `type:docs`, `type:chore`, `type:refactor`, `type:incident` | İşin türü |
| `status:*` | `status:backlog`, `status:ready`, `status:in-progress`, `status:in-review`, `status:blocked`, `status:done` | Flow'da nerede |
| `agent:*` | `agent:product-manager`, `agent:architect`, `agent:developer`, `agent:tester`, `agent:orchestrator`, `agent:human` | Sahibi kim |
| `cc:*` | `cc:product-manager`, `cc:architect`, `cc:developer`, `cc:tester`, `cc:orchestrator`, `cc:human` | Top şu an kimde |

**Enforcement**: `.github/workflows/label-check.yml` runs on every `opened|reopened|labeled|unlabeled` event. Missing category = check fail + comment with fix guidance.

**Wake labels (D2.2 — `pr_labeled` query path)**: `needs-tester-signoff`, `needs-architect-review`. Use these to wake a specific peer agent. The legacy `cc:tester` / `cc:architect` still work for legacy paths but `pr_labeled` is primary since D2.2 (ADR-0009 § 10.5.4).

## Handoff Label Discipline — the universal contract

**TL;DR**: `cc:*` = "top is here now", `agent:*` = "owner of the work". On hand-off, atomically flip BOTH with `--add-label` (next) before `--remove-label` (self) — never the reverse. Otherwise 4-cat invariant breaks and the watcher loop wakes you repeatedly on stale events.

### The contract — ADR-0015 atomic 4-flag hand-off

```bash
gh issue edit N \
  --add-label    "agent:<next>" \
  --add-label    "cc:<next>" \
  --remove-label "cc:<self>" \
  --remove-label "agent:<self>"
```

**Sıra zorunlu**: önce iki `--add-label` (4-cat invariant her t anında dolu kalır), sonra iki `--remove-label`.

Eşlik eden adımler:
- **Auto-ping**: `scripts/notify.sh -l <next-role> "[<YOU>→<NEXT>] PR #N <reason>"` (Telegram mirror)
- **Label flip + notify.sh her zaman birlikte** (ADR-0002 doctrine: "GitHub artefact + Telegram mirror")

### Terminal hand-off (Done)

Orchestrator iş Done'a girdiinde `agent:*` + `cc:*`'i temizler ve `status:done` ekler.

### Work-done-elsewhere terminal state (RETRO-024 amendment, Issue #1027)

When work for an AtilCalculator issue is tracked via a **sister PR in another repo** (cross-repo workstream per RETRO-023, Issue #1024), the canonical terminal state is:

```
type:<feature|chore|...> + status:ready + cc:human + (NO agent:*)
```

**Why this exists**: Reflexively adding `agent:*` to such an issue re-enables `claim-next-ready.sh` (ADR-0038 §Layer 2) auto-claim on it, pulling completed work back into dev lane — visible churn + ghost work on already-shipped PRs. Two live instances:

- **Cycle #1223 (orchestrator, reflexive 4-cat repair)** — orchestrator added `agent:developer` to work-done issues #1015 (S29-003) + #1017 (S29-005), reflexively "fixing the invariant". RETRO-022 regression.
- **Cycle #1253 (PM, reflexive AC-verify approval)** — PM approved RETRO-024 ACs (3/3 met) without file-state verification. Sister-pattern recursion: the very reflexive anti-pattern RETRO-024 was filed to address.

**4-cat invariant compliance**: This is a **4-cat-compliant EXCEPTION** to the universal ADR-0012 invariant. The issue has a clear `cc:human` merge gate; the absent `agent:*` signals "work tracked elsewhere, do NOT auto-claim".

**Sister-pattern**: RETRO-022 (original 4-cat gap, Issue #1023), RETRO-023 (cross-repo codification, Issue #1024), RETRO-024 (this doctrine, Issue #1027).

### §4-cat Invariant Repair Silent-Skip Rule (RETRO-024, Issue #1027)

Any 4-cat-repair script (orchestrator hygiene loop, `gh issue edit` reflexive fix, post-PR-script label normalization) MUST **silent-skip** when an issue's current labels already match the work-done-elsewhere terminal state pattern:

```
type:<*> + status:ready + cc:human + (no agent:*)
```

Adding `agent:*` to a work-done-elsewhere issue re-enables auto-claim on completed items.

**Implementation gate**: `scripts/claim-next-ready.sh` (auto-claim, ADR-0038 §Layer 2) and any future 4-cat-repair helper MUST filter `status:ready + cc:human` items from their result sets BEFORE the next claim/repair step. `silent_skip` log emission to `auto-claim.log` is required (lens d observability, TD-016/020 family).

**Sister-test**: `scripts/tests/d-retro-024-4cat-repair-silent-skip.sh` (≥5 TCs RED-first per ADR-0044), `scripts/tests/INDEX.md` row per ADR-0055 §1 Cadence Rule 1 atomic.

### Anti-patterns (sistem-wide yasaklı)

- ❌ Aynı anda `cc:tester` + `cc:developer` — top kimde belirsiz.
- ❌ Kendi `cc:*`'ini bırakmak — watcher loop seni aynı event'le tekrar uyandırır.
- ❌ Label flip'i `notify.sh` olmadan yapmak — peer GitHub'ı poll etmediği saniyelerde habersiz kalır.
- ❌ Kendine `cc:` koymak — watcher zaten seni atanan işlerde otomatik uyandırır.

## Things agents must NEVER do

- ❌ Push directly to `main`.
- ❌ Merge their own PRs.
- ❌ Modify `.github/workflows/`, secrets, branch protection without explicit human approval.
- ❌ Roll their own auth/crypto.
- ❌ Disable failing tests to make CI green.
- ❌ Edit other agents' soul files (`.claude/agents/*.md`).
- ❌ **Invent self-imposed work pauses.** Agents do NOT invent "standby", "work hours", "office hours", "iş saatleri". The only valid pause reasons are: (a) explicit human instruction in chat (verbatim, current thread), (b) explicit dependency block documented in an issue/PR (with link), (c) a heartbeat/reprime SOP step. The 09:00 standup is a *schedule*, not a work-hours gate.

